Entries.default: "It's strange, not hearing the animancers or their... colorful curses."
"Why would you be a fighter here? You could be lying on the beach."
"This place gives me the creeps."
"Arnatto. We used to play dice after dinner."
"Nothing but ash now. What a way to die."
"More ashy bodies? More sucked-out souls."
"That foot looks familiar."
"Just look that footprint. My god's huge!"
"What do you suppose they're doing in that cage?"
"You hear that? Coming from inside that cage."
"Reading Engwithan would be most useful. Perhaps you could teach me one day."
"Sure, I can read crazy languages, too. Just forgot my spectacles."
"You read the language of the gods?! You really are something else, Watcher."
"I don't suppose they're playing dead..."
"What do you think? Natural causes?"
"Wondering what killed them... Can't say I like what comes to mind."
"I've seen bigger."
"Is that who we were looking for... deader than dust by the adra pillar?"
"I like tile puzzles. I don't think I like this one."
"If I'm reading 'em right, some of these symbols are real immature."
"Reckon these symbols mean something. But Hel if I know what."
"That's a big arena. Guess they had enough folks to fill it, whenever it was built."
"What do you reckon this place was built for?"
